    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;The Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP) is a stateless application-level protocol for distributed, collaborative, hypertext information systems. This document specifies the HTTP/1.1 message syntax, message parsing, connection management, and related security concerns.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This document obsoletes portions of RFC 7230.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
